1. cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely category as the paper deals with few-shot learning in natural language domains, specifically sentiment analysis and dialog intent classification. 
2. cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also likely as the paper proposes an adaptive metric learning approach for few-shot learning. 
3. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is another possible category as the paper deals with machine learning algorithms for natural language processing tasks. 
4. cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is less likely but still possible as the paper mentions existing works that apply metric-based or optimization-based meta-learning to image domains. 
5. cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is also less likely but possible as the paper may involve the use of neural networks for few-shot learning in natural language domains.
